garlands of flowers, groups of fruit, and girls playing the cittern. \
\
The table which stood in the middle of the room was of \
\
Parian marble, and its feet, in the form of lion\'92s claws, were of \
\
silver. The seats were made of ebony, inlaid with ivory, and \
\
the feet of these also were of silver. There was no carpet or \
matting on the floor, and indeed it would have been a pity to \
hide the beautiful tesselated pavement ; but in one corner lay \
\
a soft silky rug, on which amicably reposed a slender Italian \
\
greyhound and a white Maltese shock-dog. On a silver rod \
\
suspended from the roof was perched a green parrot, and on \
another at the opposite end of the room, sat a pair of beautiful \
snowy Sicilian doves, a nightingale, and one of those abnormal \
creatures termed a white blackbird. The fourth side of the \
