Rising in the morning was a longer and less easy process than \
undressing at night, for the toilet of a Roman lady involved a \
most liberal and elaborate use of cosmetics and beautifying \
appliances of all kinds. But in the early times of the Empire \
these were not so universally employed as when, in after ages, \
the great Pagan city was tottering to its fall Camilla accordingly \
neither painted her face in the morning, nor covered it with a \
paste of ass\'92s milk for the night. She contented herself with \
paying a visit to the bath-room and being scented all over ; after \
which her hair was dressed rather elaborately by Sophronia, she \
