This query concerned her admission to full communion, for \
only the baptized, then as now, were eligible as communicants. \
During the earliest ages of the Church, all baptized persons \
received the communion as a matter of course, and if unable to \
attend church, the bread and wine were sent to them at home. \
Many kept the elements by them until their next meal, and \
