On the following day Aurelia quitted the house. She took \
a cold leave of Sophronia and Victor, but scarcely deigned to \
utter a word of farewell to Camilla, who bent down with many \
tears to kiss her robe. They supposed that she returned to \
Rome, but years elapsed before they heard of her again. \
\
It was long before the even and peaceful tenor of their lives \
was any further disturbed. A little boy was added to the \
family, to whom Victor laughingly declared that he should be \
